<h2>Add a Ferret</h2>

<%= form_for(@ferret) do |f| %>

  <label>Ferret name:</label><br>
  <%= f.text_field :name %><br>

  <label>Sex:</label><br>
  <%= f.text_field :sex %><br>

  <label>Color:</label><br>
  <%= f.text_field :color %><br>

  <label>Age:</label><br>
  <%= f.text_field :age %><br>
  
  <label>Health:</label><br>
  <%= f.text_field :health %><br>

  <label>Description:</label><br>
  <%= f.text_area :description %><br>

  <label>Found a Home?</label><br>
  <%= f.check_box :home, {}, "true", "false" %><br>
  
  <%= f.submit %>
<% end %>


<br><br>
<br><br>
<p>For the sake of this application, please define your ferret by one of the following 8 colors:</p>
<br><br>
<b>Albino, Black, Black Sable, Champagne, Chocolate, Cinnamon, Dark-Eyed White, and Sable.</b>
<br><br>
<p>You may also descrbe a pattern:</p>
<br><br>
<b>Blaze, Mitt, Mutt, Panda, Point, Roan, Solid, Standard, and Striped/Patterned.</b>
<br><br>
<em>Example: Gizmo is a Black Mitt ferret, and Coconut is a Chocolate Blaze ferret.</em>